- "stands tall" refers to the category with the highest total sales and inventory value;
- "most sold" refers to the highest total sales;
- "most valuable in stock" refers to the highest total inventory value.

- "Shining star" refers to the product with the highest total revenue;
- "Eager shoppers" refers to customers who have placed orders;
- The query focuses on the financial performance of the products.

- 'blossoming flowers' refers to products with high revenue;
- 'greenhouse' refers to a warehouse;
- 'radiance' refers to the total revenue generated by the product.

- The total revenue is calculated by multiplying the quantity sold by the price of the product;
- The total quantity available is the sum of the quantities of a product across all warehouses;
- The difference is the revenue minus the quantity available, indicating the financial performance of each product.

- "Average revenue" refers to the average total revenue generated by all variants of a product;
- "Product variants" are different versions of the same product, such as different sizes or colors;
- "Total revenue" is calculated by multiplying the total sales quantity by the product price.

- 'Top-selling' refers to the product with the highest stock quantity in the warehouse;
- 'More variants' means the product has more than one variant available;
- 'Shirts' is a specific clothing category;
- 'Warehouse A' is the name of a specific warehouse.

- 'Total sales' refers to the sum of quantities sold for each product;
- 'Product' refers to a clothing item in the inventory;
- 'Most sales' means the highest total quantity sold.

- "Best-selling" refers to products with a high number of sales and units sold;
- "Not run out of stock" means the products still have a positive stock level;
- "Inventory sky" is a metaphor for the inventory database, where products that are still in stock are like stars that are still visible.

- 'Top 3' refers to the highest-ranking categories based on total revenue;
- 'Total revenue' is the sum of all order totals within each category;
- 'Average order value' is the mean total cost of orders within each category.

- "Shining stars" refer to the top-selling products;
- "Customer segments" are groups of customers categorized based on common characteristics;
- "Revenue" is the total income generated from the sale of products.

sql:
SELECT category_name, description
FROM clothing_categories
ORDER BY category_name ASC;
